<subSubSection id="3CC75890FFF8E634FF074E7A554AF9DA" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="description">
<paragraph id="74620B1BFFF8E634FF074E7A57D6FA9A" blockId="8.[151,1437,626,1772]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="46A9D709FFF8E634FF074E7A5413FC82" bold="true" box="[199,542,786,812]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Description and Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Male (
<typeStatus id="AB66B5B9FFF8E634FDB84E7A54EBFC82" box="[632,742,786,812]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">holotype</typeStatus>
): Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="ECE6179EFFF8E634FC444E7A522BFC82" box="[900,1062,786,812]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="10.[151,255,1720,1744]" captionTargetBox="[154,1400,845,1680]" captionTargetId="figure-408@10.[140,1446,837,1693]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 1. Glyphotmethis holtzi brachypterus ssp.n., FIGURE 2. Glyphotmethis holtzi pulchripes: a, male pronotum, tegmina and hind wing from above; b, female pronotum and tegmina from above; c, male pronotum and tegmen, lateral view; d, female pronotum and tegmen, lateral view; e, male lateral view; f, female lateral view; g, apical valves of penis and cingulum, lateral view; h, ditto posterior view; i, epiphallus. Scales 1 mm." pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Figs. 1a, c, e</figureCitation>
). short and broad with distinct tubercles; prozona high its lobes distinct; lateral projections of mesozona very distinct; metazona flat, very short and broad, its lateral margins straight; angular at apex; male tegmina (
<figureCitation id="ECE6179EFFF8E634FBCF4E0A5297FCD2" box="[1039,1178,866,892]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="10.[151,255,1720,1744]" captionTargetBox="[154,1400,845,1680]" captionTargetId="figure-408@10.[140,1446,837,1693]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 1. Glyphotmethis holtzi brachypterus ssp.n., FIGURE 2. Glyphotmethis holtzi pulchripes: a, male pronotum, tegmina and hind wing from above; b, female pronotum and tegmina from above; c, male pronotum and tegmen, lateral view; d, female pronotum and tegmen, lateral view; e, male lateral view; f, female lateral view; g, apical valves of penis and cingulum, lateral view; h, ditto posterior view; i, epiphallus. Scales 1 mm." pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 1a, c, e</figureCitation>
) very short, cover the first 4–5 abdominal tergites; axillary 1 and axillary 2 veins distinct and separated; distal excision of dorsal carina of hind femur distinct; inner side of hind femur strongly darkened with dark blue; inner side of hind tibia dark blue in basal 2/3, red in apical part. Male penis valves (
<figureCitation id="ECE6179EFFF8E634FCB34EB255E7FC5A" box="[883,1002,986,1012]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="10.[151,255,1720,1744]" captionTargetBox="[154,1400,845,1680]" captionTargetId="figure-408@10.[140,1446,837,1693]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 1. Glyphotmethis holtzi brachypterus ssp.n., FIGURE 2. Glyphotmethis holtzi pulchripes: a, male pronotum, tegmina and hind wing from above; b, female pronotum and tegmina from above; c, male pronotum and tegmen, lateral view; d, female pronotum and tegmen, lateral view; e, male lateral view; f, female lateral view; g, apical valves of penis and cingulum, lateral view; h, ditto posterior view; i, epiphallus. Scales 1 mm." pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Fig. 
<quantity id="B325A6FEFFF8E634FC6C4EB255C6FC5A" box="[940,971,986,1012]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="g" value="1.0">1g</quantity>
, h
</figureCitation>
) stout apically, their apices strongly curved upwards in lateral view, widened in posterior view; lophi (
<figureCitation id="ECE6179EFFF8E634FC73496A520EFBB2" box="[947,1027,1026,1052]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="10.[151,255,1720,1744]" captionTargetBox="[154,1400,845,1680]" captionTargetId="figure-408@10.[140,1446,837,1693]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 1. Glyphotmethis holtzi brachypterus ssp.n., FIGURE 2. Glyphotmethis holtzi pulchripes: a, male pronotum, tegmina and hind wing from above; b, female pronotum and tegmina from above; c, male pronotum and tegmen, lateral view; d, female pronotum and tegmen, lateral view; e, male lateral view; f, female lateral view; g, apical valves of penis and cingulum, lateral view; h, ditto posterior view; i, epiphallus. Scales 1 mm." pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 1i</figureCitation>
) with more than 15 dense spines, posterior projection of epiphallus (
<figureCitation id="ECE6179EFFF8E634FDF44942548FFBEA" box="[564,642,1066,1092]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="10.[151,255,1720,1744]" captionTargetBox="[154,1400,845,1680]" captionTargetId="figure-408@10.[140,1446,837,1693]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 1. Glyphotmethis holtzi brachypterus ssp.n., FIGURE 2. Glyphotmethis holtzi pulchripes: a, male pronotum, tegmina and hind wing from above; b, female pronotum and tegmina from above; c, male pronotum and tegmen, lateral view; d, female pronotum and tegmen, lateral view; e, male lateral view; f, female lateral view; g, apical valves of penis and cingulum, lateral view; h, ditto posterior view; i, epiphallus. Scales 1 mm." pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 1i</figureCitation>
) concave in middle. Female: (
<figureCitation id="ECE6179EFFF8E634FC3149425283FBEA" box="[1009,1166,1066,1092]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="10.[151,255,1720,1744]" captionTargetBox="[154,1400,845,1680]" captionTargetId="figure-408@10.[140,1446,837,1693]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 1. Glyphotmethis holtzi brachypterus ssp.n., FIGURE 2. Glyphotmethis holtzi pulchripes: a, male pronotum, tegmina and hind wing from above; b, female pronotum and tegmina from above; c, male pronotum and tegmen, lateral view; d, female pronotum and tegmen, lateral view; e, male lateral view; f, female lateral view; g, apical valves of penis and cingulum, lateral view; h, ditto posterior view; i, epiphallus. Scales 1 mm." pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Figs. 1b, d, f</figureCitation>
) Prozona with distinct lobes; lateral projections of mesozona distinct; metazona flat, short and broad, only 1.4 times longer than prozona, 1.7 times wider than long; its hind margin angular; tegmina (
<figureCitation id="ECE6179EFFF8E634FC6249125235FB3A" box="[930,1080,1146,1172]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="10.[151,255,1720,1744]" captionTargetBox="[154,1400,845,1680]" captionTargetId="figure-408@10.[140,1446,837,1693]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 1. Glyphotmethis holtzi brachypterus ssp.n., FIGURE 2. Glyphotmethis holtzi pulchripes: a, male pronotum, tegmina and hind wing from above; b, female pronotum and tegmina from above; c, male pronotum and tegmen, lateral view; d, female pronotum and tegmen, lateral view; e, male lateral view; f, female lateral view; g, apical valves of penis and cingulum, lateral view; h, ditto posterior view; i, epiphallus. Scales 1 mm." pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Figs. 1b, d, f</figureCitation>
) small, reaching hardly to end of first abdominal tergite, usually shorter in other females, narrowly rounded at apex; distal excision of dorsal carina of hind femur distinct, its ventral carina clearly wavy; inner side of hind femur blackish dark blue, its anterio-ventral margin (stridulatory lamellae) with a small red spot; inner side of hind tibia dark blue in basal part; apical 1/3 turns to red.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="74620B1BFFF8E634FF07482A554AF9DA" blockId="8.[151,1437,626,1772]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
This subspecies is different from 
<taxonomicName id="B3DD7098FFF8E634FD97482B5509FAF2" authority="holtzi" authorityName="holtzi (Werner" authorityYear="1901" box="[599,772,1347,1372]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Glyphotmethis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="holtzi" subSpecies="holtzi">
<emphasis id="46A9D709FFF8E634FD97482B5509FAF2" box="[599,772,1347,1372]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">G. holtzi holtzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the shorter and broader metazona, shorter male tegmina, darker inner side of hind legs (presence of much less red color), and its distribution. It is different from 
<taxonomicName id="B3DD7098FFF8E634FF5748FB5776FA02" baseAuthorityName="Uvarov" baseAuthorityYear="1943" box="[151,379,1427,1452]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Glyphotmethis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="holtzi" subSpecies="pulchripes">
<emphasis id="46A9D709FFF8E634FF5748FB5776FA02" box="[151,379,1427,1452]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">G. holtzi pulchripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the larger body, flat shorter and broader metazona with its angular hind margin, shorter male tegmina, and its distribution. From 
<taxonomicName id="B3DD7098FFF8E634FDB448D35534FA7A" authorityName="Unal" authorityYear="2007" box="[628,825,1467,1492]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Glyphotmethis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="holtzi" subSpecies="turcicus">
<emphasis id="46A9D709FFF8E634FDB448D35534FA7A" box="[628,825,1467,1492]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">G. holtzi turcicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the larger body (especially in females), very distinct tubercles of pronotum, higher prozona and its distinct lobes, presence of lateral tubercles of mesozona, shorter and broader metazona, clearly shorter male tegmina (reaching always beyond hind knee in 
<taxonomicName id="B3DD7098FFF8E634FAF94B6356F9F9E2" authorityName="Unal" authorityYear="2007" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Glyphotmethis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="holtzi" subSpecies="turcicus">
<emphasis id="46A9D709FFF8E634FAF94B6356F9F9E2" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">G. holtzi turcicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and its distribution. The coloration of hind legs is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="B3DD7098FFF8E634FC7D4B5B52ADF9E2" baseAuthorityName="Uvarov" baseAuthorityYear="1943" box="[957,1184,1587,1612]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Glyphotmethis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="holtzi" subSpecies="pulchripes">
<emphasis id="46A9D709FFF8E634FC7D4B5B52ADF9E2" box="[957,1184,1587,1612]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">G. holtzi pulchripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="B3DD7098FFF8E634FB174B5B5391F9E2" authorityName="Unal" authorityYear="2007" box="[1239,1436,1587,1612]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Glyphotmethis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="holtzi" subSpecies="turcicus">
<emphasis id="46A9D709FFF8E634FB174B5B5391F9E2" box="[1239,1436,1587,1612]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">G. holtzi turcicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but it is different from them by the characters given above.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3CC75890FFF8E634FF074BEA5229F932" box="[199,1060,1666,1692]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="74620B1BFFF8E634FF074BEA5229F932" blockId="8.[151,1437,626,1772]" box="[199,1060,1666,1692]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
