<subSubSection id="3CC75890FFF8E634FF074BC2552EF942" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="74620B1BFFF8E634FF074BC2552EF942" blockId="8.[151,1437,626,1772]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="46A9D709FFF8E634FF074BC2575AF96A" bold="true" box="[199,343,1706,1732]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Etymology:</emphasis>
The subspecies name “brachypterus” is derived from “brachypterous” with short wing. This subspecies has the shortest male tegmina in the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
